      "explanation": "Volume confirms price trends. High volume + rising prices means many buyers are willing to pay increasingly higher prices, confirming bullish momentum. In contrast, rising prices on low volume suggests weak conviction. High volume + falling prices would signal selling pressure. This volume-price relationship is a cornerstone of technical analysis."
